<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="412" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1815,2034]" pageId="2" pageNumber="412">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,422,1815,1841]" pageId="2" pageNumber="412">Diagnosis of subgenus.</emphasis>
First flagellomere about as long as or longer than second flagellomere (
<figureCitation box="[1233,1355,1815,1841]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,655,679]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,315,631]" captionTargetId="figure-292@2.[154,1434,315,631]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. First and second flagellomeres of antenna. A. First flagellomere shorter than second flagellomere [Orthostigma (Africostigma) karkloofense Fischer, 1995]. B, C. First flagellomere as long as or longer than second flagellomere [B: O. (Whartonstigma) longipede sp. nov.; C: O. (Orthostigma) mandibulare (Tobias, 1962)]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406749/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="412">Fig. 1B, C</figureCitation>
). Mandibles small, with distinct complete transverse curved carina; its upper (first) tooth smallest, narrow and pointed, middle (second) rather long and acuminate, lower (third) tooth widest, evenly rounded. Paraclypeal fovea short, far removed from edge of eyes. Mesoscutum without midpit; notauli not developed dorsally on most part of mesoscutum; precoxal sulcus present, usually wide; propodeum usually without areas. In fore wing marginal cell not shortened; vein 2-SR absent (
<figureCitation box="[485,573,1975,2001]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1117,1141]" captionTargetBox="[149,1439,775,1093]" captionTargetId="figure-350@2.[149,1439,775,1093]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Fore wing. A. Vein 2-SR present [Orthostigma (Orthostigma) mandibulare (Tobias, 1962)]. B. Vein 2-SR absent [Orthostigma (Papuastigma) papuae sp. nov.]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406751" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4406751/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="412">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
), first and second submarginal cells fused. Metasoma more or less distinctly compressed laterally. Ovipositor sheath shorter than metasoma, often up-curved.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="413" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="413">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,313,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="413">Remarks.</emphasis>
Members of this subgenus are characterised by having the first flagellomere about as long as or longer than second flagellomere and by the absence of vein 2-SR with fused first and second submarginal cells.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
